{:title "Encrypted Secrets Vault (Imperative Shell)"
 :description "Secure storage and lifecycle management for API keys and environment credentials."
 :philosophy "Encryption at Rest (AES-GCM), Audited Access, Minimal Exposure."
 :inspired-by "Talon (Vault), 12-Factor App (Secrets)"
 :implementation-strategy
 {:storage "config/vault.edn.enc"
  :cipher "AES/GCM/NoPadding"
  :pbkdf2-iterations 100000}
 :acceptance-criteria
 ["CLI for management: `bb vault [set|get|list|rotate] <name>`."
  "Every 'get' operation triggers a signed event in the Audit Trail."
  "Secrets are injected into MCP server environments at process start only."
  "Supports an environment variable `MCP_INJECTOR_MASTER_KEY` for decryption."
  "Zero plain-text secrets stored in the codebase or git-tracked files."]
 :edge-cases
 ["Master key loss: Data is unrecoverable by design."
  "Concurrency: File locking during vault updates."
  "Secrets leak via `ps` or environment inspection (use stdin where possible)."]
 :depends-on [:audit-trail]}
